1.5 Objective of the Project
1.5.1 General Objective
To develop an intelligent, multilingual, and user-friendly mobile application that leverages artificial intelligence and real-time data to empower Ethiopian farmers with data-driven decision-making capabilities, ultimately increasing agricultural productivity, sustainability, and profitability.
1.5.2 Specific Objectives
1.	AI-Powered Crop Recommendation System: Develop algorithms analyzing location, soil, climate, and market data to recommend optimal crops with 85% accuracy for 50+ Ethiopian crops.
2.	Intelligent Disease Detection: Create computer vision models identifying 30+ common plant diseases with 90% accuracy and providing treatment recommendations in local languages.
3.	Comprehensive Farm Planning: Develop week-by-week farming guides with yield prediction accuracy of 80% and support for tracking 10+ farm activities.
4.	Multilingual Interface: Implement full support for English, Amharic, and Afaan Oromo with 95% user satisfaction in accessibility testing.
5.	Market Intelligence System: Integrate real-time market price data for 20+ major Ethiopian markets with price trends and forecasting.
6.	Weather-Based Advisory: Provide real-time weather data, 7-day forecasts, and farming recommendations based on weather conditions.
7.	Scalable Architecture: Design system supporting 100,000+ concurrent users with 99.5% uptime and cost-effective cloud infrastructure.
8.	Community Building: Create farmer community features enabling knowledge sharing and expert access.
9.	Offline Functionality: Ensure core features work without internet connectivity for farmers in remote areas.
10.	Financial Integration: Provide tools for record-keeping, expense tracking, and market value estimation.
