4. Technical Specifications
4.1 System Architecture
4.1.1 High-Level Architecture
 
4.1.2 Deployment Architecture
Cloud Infrastructure:
●	Primary Cloud: Google Cloud Platform (Firebase integration)
●	Secondary Cloud: AWS for backup and additional services
●	CDN: Cloudflare for static content delivery
●	DNS: Cloud DNS with failover routing
Container Orchestration:
●	Container Runtime: Docker
●	Orchestration: Kubernetes (GKE)
●	Service Mesh: Istio for service-to-service communication
●	Configuration: Helm charts for deployment management
Monitoring Stack:
●	Metrics: Prometheus for collection, Grafana for visualization
●	Logging: ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana)
●	Tracing: Jaeger for distributed tracing
●	Alerting: Alertmanager with Slack/Email integration


4.1.3 Security Architecture
Network Security:
●	VPC: Isolated virtual private cloud with subnets
●	Firewall: Web Application Firewall (WAF) rules
●	DDoS Protection: Cloud-based mitigation service
●	VPN: Secure access for administrators
Application Security:
●	Authentication: OAuth 2.0 with JWT tokens
●	Authorization: Role-based with attribute-based fine-tuning
●	Encryption: TLS 1.3 for transit, AES-256 for storage
●	Secrets Management: HashiCorp Vault or cloud KMS
Data Security:
●	Classification: Public, Internal, Confidential, Restricted
●	Encryption: Field-level encryption for sensitive data
●	Masking: Data masking in non-production environments
●	Retention: Automated data lifecycle management
4.2 Database Design
4.2.1 Schema Design
User Schema:
CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    phone_number VARCHAR(15) UNIQUE,
    email VARCHAR(255),
    full_name VARCHAR(255),
    location POINT,
    preferred_language VARCHAR(10),
    created_at TIMESTAMP,
    last_login TIMESTAMP,
    subscription_status VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE user_profiles (
    profile_id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id VARCHAR(36) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    farm_experience_years INTEGER,
    education_level VARCHAR(50),
    farm_size_hectares DECIMAL(10,2),
    primary_crops TEXT[],
    income_level VARCHAR(50)
);
Farm Schema:
CREATE TABLE farms (
    farm_id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id VARCHAR(36) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    farm_name VARCHAR(255),
    total_area DECIMAL(10,2),
    region VARCHAR(100),
    zone VARCHAR(100),
    woreda VARCHAR(100),
    elevation DECIMAL(10,2),
    soil_type VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE fields (
    field_id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    farm_id VARCHAR(36) REFERENCES farms(farm_id),
    field_name VARCHAR(255),
    boundaries POLYGON,
    area DECIMAL(10,2),
    soil_ph DECIMAL(3,1),
    organic_matter DECIMAL(4,2),
    last_crop VARCHAR(100),
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);
Crop Schema:
CREATE TABLE crops (
    crop_id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    local_name VARCHAR(255),
    scientific_name VARCHAR(255),
    family VARCHAR(100),
    growing_season VARCHAR(50),
    water_requirements VARCHAR(50),
    temperature_range VARCHAR(50),
    soil_preferences TEXT[]
);

CREATE TABLE crop_recommendations (
    recommendation_id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id VARCHAR(36) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    crop_id VARCHAR(36) REFERENCES crops(crop_id),
    confidence_score DECIMAL(5,2),
    reasoning TEXT,
    season VARCHAR(50),
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);
Disease Schema:
sql
CREATE TABLE diseases (
    disease_id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    scientific_name VARCHAR(255),
    common_name VARCHAR(255),
    affected_crops TEXT[],
    symptoms TEXT[],
    conditions_favoring TEXT[]
);

CREATE TABLE disease_detections (
    detection_id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id VARCHAR(36) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    image_url VARCHAR(500),
    disease_id VARCHAR(36) REFERENCES diseases(disease_id),
    confidence_score DECIMAL(5,2),
    detection_date TIMESTAMP,
    expert_validated BOOLEAN
);
Market Schema:
CREATE TABLE markets (
    market_id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    market_name VARCHAR(255),
    location POINT,
    region VARCHAR(100),
    market_days TEXT[],
    contact_phone VARCHAR(15)
);

CREATE TABLE commodity_prices (
    price_id VARCHAR(36) PRIMARY KEY,
    market_id VARCHAR(36) REFERENCES markets(market_id),
    commodity VARCHAR(100),
    unit VARCHAR(50),
    price DECIMAL(10,2),
    price_date DATE,
    source VARCHAR(100)
);
4.2.2 Indexing Strategy
Primary Indexes:
●	Users: user_id, phone_number
●	Farms: farm_id, user_id
●	Fields: field_id, farm_id
●	Crop Recommendations: recommendation_id, user_id, created_at
●	Disease Detections: detection_id, user_id, detection_date
●	Market Prices: price_id, market_id, commodity, price_date
Composite Indexes:
●	idx_user_location on users(location) for spatial queries
●	idx_farm_region on farms(region, zone, woreda)
●	idx_prices_market_date on commodity_prices(market_id, price_date DESC)
●	idx_detections_user_date on disease_detections(user_id, detection_date DESC)
Full-Text Search Indexes:
●	Crop names and descriptions
●	Disease symptoms and treatments
●	Knowledge base articles
●	Community forum posts
4.2.3 Data Partitioning
Horizontal Partitioning:
●	Users by region (sharding key: region_code)
●	Farm data by user_id hash
●	Market data by region and date range
●	Weather data by geographic grid
Vertical Partitioning:
●	User authentication data separate from profile data
●	Frequent access data in main tables, historical in archive
●	Large objects (images) in separate storage
Time-based Partitioning:
●	Market prices by month
●	Weather data by day
●	User activity logs by week
●	Disease detection history by month
4.3 API Specifications
4.3.1 REST API Design
Base URL: https://api.smartgebere.et/v1
Authentication:
http
POST /auth/login
Content-Type: application/json
{
  "phone": "+251911234567",
  "password": "********"
}

Response:
{
  "access_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...",
  "refresh_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...",
  "expires_in": 3600,
  "user": { ... }
}
User Endpoints:
http
GET    /users/{id}              # Get user profile
PUT    /users/{id}              # Update profile
POST   /users/{id}/farms        # Add farm
GET    /users/{id}/dashboard    # Get dashboard data
Farm Endpoints:
http
GET    /farms                   # List farms
POST   /farms                   # Create farm
GET    /farms/{id}              # Get farm details
PUT    /farms/{id}              # Update farm
DELETE /farms/{id}              # Delete farm
POST   /farms/{id}/fields       # Add field
GET    /farms/{id}/fields       # List fields
Crop Recommendation Endpoints:
http
POST   /recommendations/crops
Content-Type: application/json
{
  "location": {
    "lat": 9.03,
    "lng": 38.74
  },
  "soil_type": "clay_loam",
  "season": "meher",
  "preferences": {
    "market_priority": "high",
    "labor_intensity": "medium"
  }
}

Response:
{
  "recommendations": [
    {
      "crop_id": "tef-001",
      "name": "Teff",
      "confidence": 0.85,
      "reasons": ["Suitable soil", "High market demand"],
      "estimated_yield": "1.8-2.2 tons/ha",
      "estimated_profit": "ETB 45000-55000/ha"
    }
  ]
}
Disease Detection Endpoints:
http
POST   /disease/detect
Content-Type: multipart/form-data
file: plant_image.jpg
metadata: {
  "crop_type": "maize",
  "plant_part": "leaf",
  "location": {"lat": 9.03, "lng": 38.74}
}

Response:
{
  "detection_id": "det-123",
  "diseases": [
    {
      "disease_id": "mlr-001",
      "name": "Maize Leaf Rust",
      "confidence": 0.92,
      "symptoms": ["Orange pustules", "Leaf yellowing"],
      "treatments": [
        {
          "type": "chemical",
          "product": "Fungicide A",
          "application": "Spray at 2ml/liter",
          "safety": "Wear gloves and mask"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
Market Endpoints:
http
GET    /markets/prices?commodity=teff&region=oromia
GET    /markets/trends?commodity=maize&days=30
GET    /markets/nearby?lat=9.03&lng=38.74&radius=50
POST   /markets/alerts          # Set price alerts
Weather Endpoints:
http
GET    /weather/current?lat=9.03&lng=38.74
GET    /weather/forecast?lat=9.03&lng=38.74&days=7
GET    /weather/alerts?region=oromia
POST   /weather/subscriptions   # Subscribe to alerts
4.3.2 WebSocket API
Real-time Updates:
javascript
// Connect to WebSocket
const ws = new WebSocket('wss://api.smartgebere.et/ws');

// Subscribe to updates
ws.send(JSON.stringify({
  type: 'subscribe',
  channels: ['prices:teff', 'weather:alerts', 'notifications']
}));

// Handle incoming messages
ws.onmessage = (event) => {
  const data = JSON.parse(event.data);
  switch(data.channel) {
    case 'prices:teff':
      updatePriceDisplay(data.price);
      break;
    case 'weather:alerts':
      showWeatherAlert(data.alert);
      break;
    case 'notifications':
      showNotification(data.notification);
      break;
  }
};
4.3.3 GraphQL API
Schema Definition:
graphql
type Query {
  user(id: ID!): User
  farm(id: ID!): Farm
  cropRecommendations(input: RecommendationInput!): [CropRecommendation]
  diseaseDetection(image: Upload!, metadata: DetectionMetadata): DetectionResult
  marketPrices(filter: PriceFilter): [MarketPrice]
  weatherForecast(location: LocationInput!): WeatherForecast
}

type Mutation {
  createUser(input: UserInput!): User
  updateFarm(id: ID!, input: FarmInput!): Farm
  recordActivity(input: ActivityInput!): Activity
  submitDetectionReview(id: ID!, review: ReviewInput!): DetectionResult
}

type Subscription {
  priceUpdate(commodity: String!): PriceUpdate
  weatherAlert(location: LocationInput!): WeatherAlert
  newMessage(threadId: ID!): Message
}

4.4 Security Specifications
4.4.1 Authentication & Authorization
Authentication Flow:
1.	User provides phone number
2.	System sends OTP via SMS
3.	User enters OTP for verification
4.	System issues JWT token with claims
5.	Token used for subsequent API calls
JWT Token Structure:
json
{
  "header": {
    "alg": "HS256",
    "typ": "JWT"
  },
  "payload": {
    "sub": "user-123",
    "name": "Tesfaye Kebede",
    "phone": "+251911234567",
    "role": "farmer",
    "permissions": ["read:farm", "write:activity"],
    "iat": 1672531200,
    "exp": 1672534800
  },
  "signature": "HMACSHA256(...)"
}
Role-Based Access Control:
yaml
roles:
  farmer:
    permissions:
      - read:own_farm
      - write:own_activities
      - read:market_prices
      - read:weather
      - write:disease_detections
  
  extension_worker:
    inherits: farmer
    permissions:
      - read:assigned_farms
      - write:recommendations
      - read:all_market_data
  
  expert:
    inherits: extension_worker
    permissions:
      - write:disease_validations
      - write:knowledge_content
  
  admin:
    permissions:
      - read:all_data
      - write:system_config
      - manage:users
4.4.2 Data Protection
Encryption Standards:
●	In Transit: TLS 1.3 with perfect forward secrecy
●	At Rest: AES-256-GCM for database encryption
●	Key Management: Cloud KMS with automatic rotation
●	Password Hashing: Argon2id with per-user salt
Data Classification:
yaml
data_classes:
  public:
    examples: [market_prices, weather_data, crop_info]
    encryption: optional
    access: anonymous
  
  internal:
    examples: [user_activity, system_logs]
    encryption: required
    access: authenticated_users
  
  confidential:
    examples: [user_phone, farm_location, financial_data]
    encryption: required
    access: role_based
  
  restricted:
    examples: [payment_cards, government_ids]
    encryption: required + tokenization
    access: strict_role_based + audit
4.4.3 Security Monitoring
Real-time Monitoring:
●	Suspicious login attempts
●	Unusual API usage patterns
●	Data export attempts
●	Permission escalation tries
Security Logging:
json
{
  "timestamp": "2025-01-20T10:30:00Z",
  "event": "authentication",
  "user": "user-123",
  "ip": "196.188.0.1",
  "user_agent": "SmartGebere/1.0",
  "success": true,
  "metadata": {
    "method": "phone_otp",
    "location": "Addis Ababa",
    "device_id": "device-abc"
  }
}
Incident Response:
1.	Detection via automated alerts
2.	Triage and classification
3.	Containment procedures
4.	Investigation and analysis
5.	Eradication and recovery
6.	Post-incident review
